{
  "texts": [
    "Related work and Conclusions round the paper out in Sections VII and VIII respectively.",
    "An AI/ML model card should tightly relate to the AI/ML model it describes -always accessible to lend clarity on what the model is, how it has been and will continue to be used.",
    "This is a tall order in an environment where AI/ML Models can be arbitrarily downloaded, transformed, and run anywhere.",
    "We have the benefit of exploring the utility of model cards by constraining the working environment to the broader ICICLE cyberinfrastructure environment.",
    "This execution environment is underpinned by the Tapis hosted API platform [18].In this section we provide the foundation underlying Patra's dynamic model card framework."
  ]
}